('curvebal','Curve Ball',2,false,false,false,false,'Note that player 1 and player 2 share a set of controls.  During an inning change, player 1 swaps places with player 2 and vice-versa. The batter buttons are globally labeled ''Bat Control and Runners Speed''  and the pitch controls are labeled ''Speed of Pitch and Curve''.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('cybsled','Cyber Sled (US)',1,false,false,false,false,'This game used dual analog flight sticks.  The Fire and Missile buttons are mirrored on both sticks, while the view point button is a lighted button on the control panel.  It should be noted that this game was only sold as a dual cabinet with two boards linked together for head-2-head action, however due to limitations mame only emulates the first board and will probably never emulate the dual mode.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
