('dangar','Dangar - Ufo Robo (12/1/1986)',2,true,false,false,true,'The transform button allows you to split the main ship into several smaller ships.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('dangerz','Danger Zone',1,false,false,false,false,'This game does NOT use a trackball in real life.  Instead, it uses quite possibly the most unique control ever.  Two immovable trigger sticks are mounted on a panel attached to the monitor.  When you try to move the sticks, they remain rigid and actually tilt the monitor!  The gameplay screen then scrolls depending upon where you tilt the monitor to.  This gives the illusion of the player looking through a window onto the battle field.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('indyheat','Danny Sullivan''s Indy Heat',3,false,false,false,false,'Player 1 is the Red car, Player 2 is the White car (light grey-ish), Player 3 is the Blue car.  Mame by default maps the pedal and the turbo button to the same button input (button 1).  If you leave it this way, to use turbo, release the button and press it again.  To enter service mode, hold down the blue turbo button and then press the service key (F2).',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
