('wfortune','Wheel Of Fortune',3,false,false,false,true,'This game is just like the tv show.  Everyone spins the same wheel which is mapped to player one''s controls.  The wheel is a glorified, oversized, spinner with a wof ''wheel'' sticker on top of it.  When not spinning, the wheel moves the cursor while the select button selects the action highlighted. It should be noted that the wheel won''t spin left while in ''spin the wheel'' mode.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('whodunit','Who Dunit (version 8.0)',2,true,false,false,false,'This game actually used a mounted lightgun (or light shotgun I should say) but the ''other'' flag that we generally tag onto special controls isn''t needed as the game plays just fine with an unmounted lightgun and there have been arcade conversions utilizing unmounted guns.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wildfang','Wild Fang / Tecmo Knight',2,false,false,false,false,'Special transforms your warrior into a small guy riding a tiger',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('moo','Wild West C.O.W.-Boys of Moo Mesa (ver EA)',4,false,false,false,false,'Combinations of Jump, Shoot and a Direction perform various special moves.  They are listed on screen as you run across them.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('willow','Willow (USA)',2,true,false,false,true,'Holding attack button will increase the power of the attack',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wizdfire','Wizard Fire (Over Sea v2.1)',2,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wow','Wizard of Wor',2,false,false,true,false,'The original game had a fire button on the left and a ball top joystick on the left.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wolfpack','Wolf Pack (prototype)',1,false,false,true,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wboy','Wonder Boy (set 1, 315-5177)',2,true,false,false,true,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wbml','Wonder Boy in Monster Land (Japan New Ver., MC-8123, 317-0043)',2,true,false,false,true,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wbeachvl','World Beach Volley (set 1)',4,false,false,false,false,'3rd button is mapped but not known what it does',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wcbowl','World Class Bowling (v1.66)',4,true,false,false,true,'When looking in the tab menu it would seem the game is only 2 player, however it is a 4 player game with each player entering the game by pressing the Player1 start button (on the control panel it is just a Start button).  Player 2 start button is mapped but doesn?t do anything',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wcbowldx','World Class Bowling Deluxe (v2.00)',4,true,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wseries','World Series: The Season',2,false,false,false,false,'This is a simultaneous 2 player alternating game; a player is on the left side when pitching, on the right side when batting.  The aim button is shown with two physical buttons wired to one pin in the schematics.  All buttons are on one input port in the machine; mame puts them all as player 1 inputs, but on the 2 player game, the aim button(s) is more like a player 2 button.  (On a one player game, all inputs are like player 1 inputs.)',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wsf','World Soccer Finals',4,false,false,false,false,'A and B both do varouis things, depending upon the situation.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wtennis','World Tennis',2,true,false,false,true,'The label for the button is unknown.  I took an educated guess and take full responsibility for it''s accuracy.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wwfsstar','WWF Superstars (Europe)',2,false,false,false,false,'Press button A to punch, button B to kick.    As with all WWF games, the two buttons do a number of things by pressing different combinations at different times including pin, ect.  If anyone wishes to make a list please do so here.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wwfwfest','WWF WrestleFest (US set 1)',4,false,false,false,false,'The A and B buttons do various things depending upon the wrestler and the situation.  Generally when you can do something special you recieve a message on the screen on how to do so.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('wwfmania','WWF: Wrestlemania (rev 1.30 08/10/95)',2,false,false,true,false,'This game has the same mame-related layout problems as the mk games.  The X pattern applies.  Press punch and kick at the same time to run.      Note that the punch buttons are on the top row and the kick buttons are on the bottom, unlike the mk games and similar to sf games.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xmen','X-Men (4 Players ver UBB)',4,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xmvsf','X-Men Vs. Street Fighter (Euro 961004)',2,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xmcota','X-Men: Children of the Atom (Euro 950105)',2,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xsleena','Xain''d Sleena',2,true,false,false,true,'Pressing the jump button while already in the air will do a second jump boost.  Much of the data on this game is purely speculative as it is a copy of Solar Warrior.  It is assumed that they use the same labels.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xenophob','Xenophobe',3,false,false,true,false,'This trigger stick has two thumb buttons in additon to the normal fire button.  The left and right buttons each do over a dozen things, with what they do depending upon the message displayed on the screen at the time.  They are appropriately labeled ''left button'' and ''right button'' on the screen.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xevious','Xevious (Namco)',2,true,false,false,true,'The labels on the original cpo are the ones in this entry, however they don''t really apply to what the buttons do.  Button 1 shoots and Button 2 Fires bombs. Because of this the button labels may be swapped as I don''t have access to a real machine.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('xybots','Xybots (rev 2)',2,false,false,false,false,'This game used a twist stick, not to be confused with a rotary mechanical stick.  Basically you can twist the stick left and right for two additional inputs.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('yesnoj','Yes/No Sinri Tokimeki Chart',2,false,false,true,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('yiear','Yie Ar Kung-Fu (set 1)',2,true,false,false,true,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('yosakdon','Yosaku To Donbei (set 1)',2,true,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('yuyugogo','Yuuyu no Quiz de GO!GO! (Japan)',2,false,false,true,false,'Game in Japanese.  No references available.  Buttons relate to the numbers on the screen.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zaxxon','Zaxxon (set 1)',2,true,false,false,true,'The fire button is also placed on the control panel.  The button on the trigger stick lights up when it''s time for you to do some shooting.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zerohour','Zero Hour',2,true,false,false,true,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zeropnt','Zero Point (set 1)',2,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zeropnt2','Zero Point 2',2,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zerowing','Zero Wing (single players)',2,true,false,true,true,'Control wise this game is pretty standard, but the game''s claim to fame is the wording of the translated text, or more accurately the poor wording of the translated text.  This is commonly referred to as ''Engrish''  Ever wondered where the ''All Your Base Are Belong To Us.'' line comes from?  It''s this game.  So for a good laugh check it out.  All your controls are belong to us!!!!',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zerozone','Zero Zone',2,false,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zigzag','Zig Zag (Galaxian hardware, set 1)',2,true,false,false,true,'This game is a pirated version of digdug.  With the execption of a new title, the game plays exactly the same.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zingzip','Zing Zing Zip',2,false,false,true,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zoar','Zoar',2,true,false,false,false,'This is probably the only 2d shooter ever to utilize the z axis.  Instead of being able to speedup or slowdown with the up and down directions, these directions allow you to make the craft raise or lower to the ground.  The top speed key doesn''t appear to do anything until you try to move left or right.  When you do you will move much more quickly.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zodiack','Zodiack',2,true,false,false,true,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zombraid','Zombie Raid (US)',2,false,false,false,false,'Controls were sawed-off shotguns with pump action reload, this is mapped to button 2',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zookeep','Zoo Keeper (set 1)',2,true,false,true,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zunkyou','Zunzunkyou No Yabou (Japan)',2,true,false,false,false,'',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
('zwackery','Zwackery',2,true,false,true,false,'This game has an identical control panel layout as discs of tron.  Unfortunately due to the fact that it''s a platformer, it is extremely akward to play unless you have those exact controls.',ARRAY[]::TEXT[]),
